# UitKit — Dual License

Copyright © 2026 Tushar Aggarwal · [Uitbreiden](https://uitbreiden.com/)

UitKit is dual-licensed depending on the file type. This split keeps the
knowledge base freely shareable while ensuring the software around it stays
open over the network.

---

## Code — GNU Affero General Public License v3.0

The full text of the AGPL-3.0 license is in [LICENSE-CODE](LICENSE-CODE).

**What's covered:** all executable code in this repository, including:

- The Astro website under `site/`
- Hook scripts (`hooks/**/*.sh`, `hooks/**/*.py`)
- Helper scripts under `scripts/`
- Plugin manifest and any TypeScript/JavaScript under `.claude-plugin/`
- The npm package entry points (when the project is published to npm)
- Any other source code added in the future

**What this means in plain English:**

- You may use, modify, and distribute the code freely.
- If you modify the code and run it as a network service (e.g. host a fork of
  the site), you must make your modified source available to the users of that
  service.
- Derivative works must be released under AGPL-3.0 or a compatible license.

If you need a different licensing arrangement for commercial use, contact
[ceo@uitbreiden.com](mailto:ceo@uitbreiden.com).

