---

## Why the split

A pure AGPL repo would restrict downstream content reuse in ways that hurt the
project's mission: an Anthropic employee, a community blogger, or a vendor
should be able to quote a UitKit skill in their own documentation without
having to release everything they ship under AGPL.

A pure permissive license (MIT, Apache, CC-BY) would allow a commercial vendor
to fork the site, host it as a network service, and never contribute back. The
AGPL on the software prevents that specific failure mode.

Splitting code and content gives each piece the right license for its purpose:
strong copyleft for code, attribution-only for content.

